{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1b46f6d6-c021-4360-955b-41819feefc71","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing your .dmp file! None of my specialized skills cover dump *analysis* (only collection), but here's what you can do:\n\n**Recommended tools:**\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform CLI):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Then inside the REPL:\n   - `clrstack` — managed call stack of the crashing thread\n   - `pe` (PrintException) — show the exception that caused the crash\n   - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n   - `threads` — list all managed threads\n\n2. **WinDbg + SOS** (Windows, more powerful):\n   - Load the dump, then `.loadby sos clr` or `.loadby sos coreclr`\n   - `!pe` / `!clrstack` / `!threads`\n\n3. **Visual Studio** — open the .dmp directly for a guided experience.\n\n**Would you like me to:**\n- Walk you through a `dotnet-dump analyze` session interactively here (if you can upload or provide the path to the .dmp)?\n- Help you interpret specific output you've already collected?\n\nLet me know the .NET version and OS, and I can tailor the steps further.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"73b5cd4f-9fee-42f6-beb2-e2828d816c7b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me look at the available skills to see if any are relevant.\n\nLooking at the available skills:\n- `dump-collect` - This is for *collecting* crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. The description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\"\n- `android-tombstone-symbolication` - For Android tombstone files, not .dmp files\n- `apple-crash-symbolication` - For Apple .ips crash logs, not .dmp files\n\n\n- None of the available skills can help with analyzing .dmp files, so I'll need to guide them directly on the best tools for this—either `dotnet-dump analyze` for a cross-platform approach, or WinDbg with SOS on Windows, or lldb with SOS on Linux/macOS.","outputTokens":617,"requestId":"5019:18FE2C:21EE0F:2A5A28:69F55588"},"id":"5ce9344c-2af1-479d-96a7-33725c6f9a58","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:38:31.702Z","parentId":"0c195906-fcd2-47bc-9dbb-8e51a1f3116e"}
